Argo CD Notification

ShinChul Bang
Jan 20 · 9 min read

Study a library for working with Slack or Email from Argo CDs.

Predecessor:

  • A Kubernetes cluster must be configured.
  • The Argo CD must be set up in your Kubernetes cluster.

Order (Summary):

  • Create Slack App: https://api.slack.com/apps?new_app=1
  • Enter OAuth & Permissions from left menu
  • Scope 설정(chat:write:bot)
  • Slack App Install
  • OAuth token confirmation
  • Apply manifest to notification on k8s cluster with the following command
kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj-labs/argocd-notifications/stable/manifests/install.yaml
  • Modify the secret manifest contents with the following command
kubectl apply -f - << EOF 
apiVersion: v1 
kind: Secret 
metadata:   
  name: argocd-notifications-secret 
stringData:   
  notifiers.yaml: |     
    slack:       
      token: <위에서 생성했던 Slack app의 OAuth token 입력> 
type: Opaque 
EOF
  • Change the ConfigMap contents with the following command to set up notifications when Argo CD Sync
kubectl apply -f - << EOF 
apiVersion: v1 
kind: ConfigMap 
metadata:   
  name: argocd-notifications-cm 
data:   
  config.yaml: |     
    triggers:       
      - name: on-sync-succeeded         
        enabled: true 
EOF
  • Query argo cd app to apply argo cd notification
$ kubectl get app -n argocd 
NAME                     AGE 
test-app                  1h 
...
  • Add annotation to apply argo cd notification to test-app with the following command
kubectl patch app test-app -n argocd -p '{"metadata":{"annotations":{"recipients.argocd-notifications.argoproj.io":"slack:<내 슬랙 채널명>"}}}' --type merge

Create Slack App

First https://api.slack.com/apps?new_app=1 be connected to.

Then you can see the screen as below.

Click the 'Create New App' button to create a Slack App for your Argo CD.

If you click button, you can see the window as below.

Enter the name of the app you want to create in 'App Name'. If you want to change it later, you can change it so you don't have to worry about it.

In 'Development Slack Workspace', specify the Slack Workspace to set the Slack App.

I set the following:

If everything is correct, click the 'Create App' button to create the Slack App.

After creating a Slack App, it will redirect to the screen below.

From this screen, click on the 'OAuth & Permissions' menu located on the left menu bar.

As the page moves, scroll down a bit.

Looking down, there are Scopes, where you can decide which permissions you want to use through the OAuth Token in the Slack App.

Click 'Add an OAuth Scope' button to set the permissions of the OAuth Token.

We will create an App that acts as a notification for a particular Slack channel, so chat:write:botselect the permission.

chat:write:botIs to create a bot account in Slack Workspace and authorize it to enter messages on the Slack channel through this bot account.

Now if you scroll back to the top, you'll see that the 'Install App to Workspace' button turns green and is clickable.

Click the 'Install App to Workspace' button to see the screen below.

Install our app on the Slack channel.

Make sure the permissions we have granted are correct and click on the 'Allow' button.

If you install Slack App, you can check OAuth Access Token as below.

This token will be used later for the Argo CD Notification Secret.

Set up Argo CD Notification on a Kubernetes Cluster

Follow the instructions below to set up.

Argo CD Notifications

First, apply the manifests required for Argo CD Notification to the cluster with the following command.

$ kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj-labs/argocd-notifications/stable/manifests/install.yaml

Next, run the following command to modify the security manifest.

Here we use the token of the Slack App we created.

kubectl apply -f - << EOF
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: argocd-notifications-secret
stringData:
  notifiers.yaml: |
    slack:
      token: xoxp-blah-blah-lorem-ipsum-foo-bar
type: Opaque
EOF

In addition, the following command modifies the ConfigMap manifest to catch the Slack channel by triggering the Sync success of the Argo CD.

kubectl apply -f - << EOF
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: argocd-notifications-cm
data:
  config.yaml: |
    triggers:
      - name: on-sync-succeeded
        enabled: true
EOF

Finally, you need to modify the metadata in the manifest contents of the application to which notifications are distributed from the Argo CD.

To find an application to apply notification to, you can use the following command:

$ kubectl get app -n argocd
NAME                     AGE
test-app                  1h
...

test-appI found an application called with the command :

Let's apply argo cd notification to this application.

Run the following command: The Slack channel to send the notification to generalis specified as.

kubectl patch app test-app -n argocd -p '{"metadata":{"annotations":{"recipients.argocd-notifications.argoproj.io":"slack:general"}}}' --type merge

Check Notification Action

Now let's sync the test-app to see if there are any notifications on the general channel on Slack.

When you sync, you can see that the Slack App we created below sends a notification.
